article_title: Tim Tebow Coming To SD For Christian Athlete Event
article_text:
Sioux Falls, SD

Former NFL quarterback and Heisman Trophy winner Tim Tebow is coming to South Dakota to attend award ceremonies for Christian athletes.



The 27-year-old Tebow is scheduled to attend the "Night of Champions" ceremonies hosted by the South Dakota Fellowship of Christian Athletes in Rapid City and Sioux Falls in April.



Tebow was selected in the first round of the NFL draft by the Denver Broncos. He played three seasons with the Broncos and the New York Jets. He is currently a college football analyst.



Tickets are $30 for the events and go on sale March 9.
